---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 16, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Avela Travel"
  description="How Avela Travel collects, uses, and protects the information you share with us."
>
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="legal-hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <div class="legal-inner">
      <p>
        Avela Travel ("Avela," "we," "us," or "our") is a concierge travel
        service based in Nosara, Costa Rica. This Privacy Policy explains what
        information we collect when you visit avela.travel or contact us, how we
        use it, and the choices you have. By using our website or sharing
        information with us, you agree to the practices described here.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We only collect what we need to plan your trip and reply to you.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you give us directly.</strong> When you fill out
          our contact form, send us an email, message us on WhatsApp, or
          subscribe to our newsletter, you may share your name, email address,
          phone number, travel dates, group size, budget range, preferred
          villas or experiences, and any notes you choose to include.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> Like most
          websites, we log basic technical data such as your IP address,
          browser type, device type, referring page, and pages visited. We use
          Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is privacy-friendly and does not
          place tracking cookies or fingerprint visitors.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your inquiry and prepare a personalized travel proposal.</li>
        <li>Coordinate bookings with the villas, chefs, guides, and partners involved in your trip.</li>
        <li>Send you trip-related communications during planning and while you are with us in Nosara.</li>
        <li>
          With your consent, send occasional updates about new villas, seasonal
          availability, and Nosara travel ideas. You can unsubscribe from these
          at any time using the link in each email.
        </li>
        <li>Improve our website, content, and services.</li>
        <li>Comply with applicable legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information, and we do not share it with
        third parties for their own marketing purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Who we share information with</h2>
      <p>
        To plan and deliver your trip, we share only the details necessary with
        trusted partners. These may include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Villa owners and property managers in Nosara.</li>
        <li>Private chefs, surf instructors, tour operators, drivers, and wellness providers we coordinate on your behalf.</li>
        <li>
          Service providers who help us operate the website and communicate with
          you, such as Formspree (contact form delivery), our email and
          newsletter platform, hosting providers, and Cloudflare (web infrastructure and analytics).
        </li>
        <li>Authorities or other parties when required by law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Avela operates from Costa Rica. Some of the service providers we use
        process data in the United States, the European Union, or other
        jurisdictions. By contacting us or using our site, you understand your
        information may be processed outside your country of residence.
      </p>

      <h2>5. How long we keep your information</h2>
      <p>
        We keep inquiry and trip-planning records for as long as needed to
        provide our service, plus a reasonable period after to handle follow-up
        bookings, accounting, and legal obligations. Newsletter subscriber data
        is kept until you unsubscribe.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct,
        delete, or export the personal information we hold about you, to
        withdraw consent, or to object to certain processing. To exercise these
        rights, email us at
        <a href="mailto:hello@avela.travel">hello@avela.travel</a>. We will
        respond within a reasonable timeframe.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use a minimal set of cookies and similar technologies that are
        necessary for the site to function. We do not use advertising cookies
        or cross-site tracking. Your browser settings allow you to block or
        delete cookies at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable steps to protect the information you share with us,
        including encrypted connections (HTTPS) and limiting access to authorized
        team members. No method of transmission over the internet is fully
        secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Our services are intended for adults planning travel. We do not
        knowingly collect personal information from anyone under 16. If you
        believe a child has shared information with us, contact us and we will
        delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we
        will revise the "Last updated" date above. Material changes will be
        flagged on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your information?
      </p>
      <p>
        Avela Travel<br />
        Nosara, Guanacaste, Costa Rica<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:hello@avela.travel">hello@avela.travel</a><br />
        WhatsApp: <a href="https://wa.me/50687297620">+506 8729 7620</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-hero {
    background: var(--green-deep);
    color: var(--warm-cream);
    padding: clamp(100px, 14vw, 160px) var(--gutter) clamp(40px, 6vw, 70px);
  }

  .legal-hero-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-hero .eyebrow {
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .legal-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5vw, 64px);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255, 241, 207, 0.55);
  }

  .legal-section {
    padding: clamp(60px, 9vw, 120px) var(--gutter);
    background: var(--cream);
  }

  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: rgba(19, 18, 16, 0.78);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .legal-inner h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 28px);
    color: var(--dark);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-inner p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-inner ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-inner li {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }

  .legal-inner a {
    color: var(--brown);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
  }

  .legal-inner a:hover {
    color: var(--amber-deep);
  }

  .legal-inner strong {
    color: var(--dark);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
